From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 00:30:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] net: stmmac: dwmac-motorcomm: Fix compilation errors and
 panics on kernel 6.18

This patch fixes compilation issues and kernel panics that occur when
backporting the motorcomm driver by Yao Zi to the 6.18 kernel.

This patch isn't necessary for kernel 6.19

The fixes include:
1. Replacing stmmac_plat_dat_alloc() with devm_kzalloc() for platform
   data allocation, fixing compatibility with the older kernel structure.
2. Replacing the newer axi_blen_regval bitmask with the axi_blen array,
   as axi_blen_regval is not present in 6.18 stmmac platform data headers.
3. Explicitly initializing various stmmac_plat_dat fields, such as setting
   force_sf_dma_mode = 1, configuring queue constraints (tx/rx queues = 1,
   disabling use_prio), and defining filter entries and max MTU. This
   prevents null pointer dereferences and uninitialized configurations that
   lead to kernel panics during the dwmac driver startup on older kernels.

Signed-off-by: c127dev <contact@c127.dev>
---
 .../ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-motorcomm.c | 20 ++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-motorcomm.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-motorcomm.c
index 61a197cd34ab..f149e3d93da4 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-motorcomm.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-motorcomm.c
@@ -210,7 +210,7 @@ motorcomm_default_plat_data(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 	struct plat_stmmacenet_data *plat;
 	struct device *dev = &pdev->dev;
 
-	plat = stmmac_plat_dat_alloc(dev);
+	plat = devm_kzalloc(dev, sizeof(*plat), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!plat)
 		return NULL;
 
@@ -234,11 +234,25 @@ motorcomm_default_plat_data(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 	plat->dma_cfg->eame		= true;
 	plat->dma_cfg->mixed_burst	= true;
 
+	plat->force_sf_dma_mode = 1;
+	plat->multicast_filter_bins = 256; /* HASH_TABLE_SIZE is 256 usually */
+	plat->unicast_filter_entries = 1;
+	plat->maxmtu = JUMBO_LEN;
+
+	plat->tx_queues_to_use = 1;
+	plat->rx_queues_to_use = 1;
+
+	plat->tx_queues_cfg[0].use_prio = false;
+	plat->rx_queues_cfg[0].use_prio = false;
+	plat->rx_queues_cfg[0].pkt_route = 0x0;
+
 	plat->axi->axi_wr_osr_lmt	= 1;
 	plat->axi->axi_rd_osr_lmt	= 1;
 	plat->axi->axi_mb		= true;
-	plat->axi->axi_blen_regval	= DMA_AXI_BLEN4 | DMA_AXI_BLEN8 |
-					  DMA_AXI_BLEN16 | DMA_AXI_BLEN32;
+	plat->axi->axi_blen[0]		= 4;
+	plat->axi->axi_blen[1]		= 8;
+	plat->axi->axi_blen[2]		= 16;
+	plat->axi->axi_blen[3]		= 32;
 
 	plat->bus_id		= pci_dev_id(pdev);
 	plat->phy_interface	= PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_GMII;
